---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Methodology | Constitution Atlas" description="Editorial methodology for the constitutional knowledge base.">
	<section class="page-intro">
		<p class="eyebrow">Methodology</p>
		<h1>How the site should be maintained as it grows.</h1>
		<p class="page-intro__summary">
			Scalability here depends on editorial discipline. Each current-affairs page should identify a constitutional
			question, link to the relevant provisions, cite sources, and carry a clear status label.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="page-copy prose">
		<h2>Source hierarchy</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Official constitutional text and government publications</li>
			<li>Supreme Court and High Court judgments</li>
			<li>Policy explainers and legislative analysis</li>
			<li>Reputable journalism for event context</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>Publishing rules</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Every page must disclose sources.</li>
			<li>Every live explainer must define the constitutional issue in plain English.</li>
			<li>Pages should be updated over time rather than replaced by disconnected news posts.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</Layout>
